ing to climb a mountain keeps walking around the mountain to find the best =
path to climb, one may eventually forget that the goal is to climb the moun=
tain and be stuck at the base forever. Similarly, one who keeps learning th=
is and that forever may forget that reaching god is the final goal and get =
stuck. So compassionate masters may sometimes remind us of the final goal.
=

