.

Swami Vivekananda said at a San Francisco class: "I am the disciple of a=
 man who could not write his own name, and I am not worthy to undo his shoe=
s. How often have I wished I could take my intellect and throw it into the =
Ganges!"

Student said, "But, Swami, that is the part of you I like best."
=

